metadata.name: U-Type #001
metadata.description:
'Uncontextual Typologies' is a collection of semi-architectural concepts created and represtened as artworks with geometric shapes enhanced by sunlight and shadows.

You as a viewer of this artwork, dont have to think about its reason of creation because there is no existing state and history of the site where these typologies are located so that this enables you to view it as a pure architectural aesthetic.
